# SDD Custom Rules
#
# This file overrides the default SDD skill behavior for this project.
# Rename to `modscape-spec.custom.md` to activate (remove the `.example` suffix).
# Rules defined here take PRIORITY over the built-in SDD skill instructions.
#
# Delete or comment out any section you don't need to customize.
#
# SDD Directory Structure:
#   .modscape/
#   ├── modscape-spec.custom.md         This file (project-wide SDD custom rules)
#   ├── rules.custom.md                 Data model conventions (optional)
#   ├── changes/
#   │   └── <name>/                     Work folder per pipeline (temporary)
#   │       ├── spec.md                 Business requirements
#   │       ├── spec-config.yaml        Main YAML mapping for this spec
#   │       ├── spec-model.yaml         Work-scoped data model (extracted + new tables)
#   │       ├── design.md               Design decisions + real-data findings
#   │       └── tasks.md                Implementation task list
#   ├── archives/
#   │   └── YYYY-MM-DD-<name>/          Archived work folders
#   └── specs/                          Permanent spec storage (overridable — see ## Spec Directory)
#       ├── <table-id>/
#       │   └── spec.md                 Permanent business spec per table
#       ├── _questions.yaml             Q&A history
#       ├── _glossary.yaml              Business term definitions
#       └── _context.yaml              Cross-project architectural decisions
#
# SDD Workflow:
#   /modscape:spec:requirements           → create changes/<name>/spec.md
#   /modscape:spec:design <name>          → design spec-model.yaml, generate design.md
#   /modscape:spec:tasks <name>           → generate tasks.md from finalized design
#   /modscape:spec:implement <name>       → implement tasks one by one
#   /modscape:spec:archive <name>         → merge into main YAML, sync specs/<table-id>/spec.md, move to archives/

## Overall Policy

# Uncomment and edit to set project-wide defaults:
# - This project uses Data Vault 2.0 modeling patterns.
# - Target tool is always dbt (BigQuery). Do not ask the user to choose.
# - All models must be in the `analytics` dbt project.

## Communication

# Set the language for all AI responses in this project.
# Uncomment one of the lines below:
# - Always respond in Japanese.
# - Always respond in English.

## Main YAMLs

# Default main YAML(s) for this project.
# Used when spec-config.yaml does not exist yet.
# If your project has multiple domain YAMLs, list them all.
# The AI will ask which tables belong to which YAML during design.
#
# Main YAMLs:
#   - models/sales/HR.yaml
#   - models/finance/Finance.yaml

## spec.md Extensions

# Additional required fields for spec.md in this project:
# - Add a `## SLA` section with update frequency (e.g., "Daily at 06:00 JST")
# - Add a `## Compliance` section for data governance tags (e.g., GDPR, PII)

## tasks.md Format

# Additional phases or tasks to append to every generated tasks.md:
# ## Phase 5: Data Contracts
# - [ ] Publish data contract for `<mart_table>`
# - [ ] Notify downstream consumers of schema

## Implementation Output

# Code generation preferences (used by /modscape:spec:implement):
# - Target tool: dbt (BigQuery)
# - Output directory for staging models: models/staging/
# - Output directory for core models: models/core/
# - Output directory for mart models: models/mart/
# - Schema test file: models/schema.yml
# - Add Japanese comments to generated SQL
# - Use dbt-expectations for all test assertions
# - dbt project name: analytics

## Naming Conventions

# Table ID → physical name mapping rules:
# - Staging: stg_<source>_<entity>
# - Fact: fct_<event>
# - Dimension: dim_<entity>
# - Mart: mart_<domain>_<metric>

## Spec Directory

# Override the default permanent spec storage directory.
# Default: .modscape/specs
# Set this when your project stores specs outside the .modscape/ tree
# (e.g., alongside dbt models or in a shared docs directory).
# All archive operations (spec sync, _questions.yaml, _glossary.yaml, _context.yaml)
# will use this path instead of the default.
#
# - Spec directory: docs/specs

## Coverage Policy

# Minimum documentation coverage threshold (0-100).
# When set, /modscape:spec:check shows a coverage warning for tables below this threshold,
# and /modscape:spec:archive prompts for confirmation before merging if coverage is below it.
# Remove or comment out this section to disable coverage checks entirely.
#
# - Minimum documentation coverage: 70%
